methods.consumeRecord:
Consume a Kafka record, producing zero or more rows in the output.

:param record: (org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer.ConsumerRecord<?,?>) - the record received from KafkaConsumer.poll(Duration).
methods.make:
:param writer: io.deephaven.tablelogger.TableWriter<?>
:param kafkaPartitionColumn: java.lang.String
:param offsetColumnName: java.lang.String
:param timestampColumnName: java.lang.String
:param valueColumns: java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>
:return: io.deephaven.kafka.ingest.JsonConsumerRecordToTableWriterAdapter

text:
Converts a consumer record containing JSON serialized objects to a Deephaven row.

 After processing explicit mappings for fields; the JSON record is searched for exact matches of the key.
